{
  "doc_id": "prion_0507",
  "text": "A 49-year-old man developed ataxia, myoclonic jerks, cortical blindness, and dementia.\nIn 3 1/2 months, he rapidly deteriorated and died.\nClinical and autopsy diagnosis confirmed Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease.\nThe eyes were examined and bilateral optic atrophy was noted.\nNo other ocular changes were noted.\nOptic atrophy had not been noted before death.",
